b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48443.htm)  [Next](sbe48445.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n61\\. On account of rectification.\n\nThe text 'from the seat of the Hot _ri_ he sets right the wrong Udgiha' shows\nthat the meditation is necessarily required for the purpose of correcting\nwhatever mistake may be made in the Udgitha. This also proves that the\nmeditation is an integral part of the sacrificial performance.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 62. And on account of the declaration of a quality being common to all\nthe Vedas](sbe48445.htm)\n\n"